<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2706] Unable to use increment operator on static variables prefixed by class name</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2706</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cannot use increment operator on static variables when prefixed by class name.  For instance (&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#43;&amp;#43;counter&lt;/tt&gt;) works fine but (&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#43;&amp;#43;ClassName.counter&lt;/tt&gt;) does not.  This is a runtime, not compile time issue. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The exception that is reported is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.lang.VerifyError: (class: StaticIncrementBug, method: main signature: 
([Ljava/lang/String;)V) Unable to pop operand off an empty stack.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It looks like incorrect byte code which is corrupting the stack.  That&apos;s just a guess, I don&apos;t know enough about groovy internals to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
